{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "mixed_stencil",
    "description": "M3 cadence-partition fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §6.1; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.7; bead ess-my4.3.6): the canonical THREE-cadence stencil. An FVM-diffusion RHS D(u[i])/dt = sum_{k in stencil} Kdiff[i] * coeff[i,k] * (u[nbr[i,k]] - u[i]) whose dependency-partition pass splits across all three classes and fires the frontier cut at BOTH thresholds. `nbr` (neighbour index table) and `coeff` (geometric coefficients) are CONST topology — arrayed parameters that are document literals, folded into the artifact at compile. `Kdiff` is a `discrete` diffusivity field reloaded on a schedule — DISCRETE, materialized into a per-event buffer the hot path reads as a constant. `u` is the integrated state — CONTINUOUS. The KEY propagation rule is exercised by the nested gather `index(u, index(nbr,i,k))`: the inner neighbour-selection `index(nbr,i,k)` classes CONST (topology) while the outer value-load `index(u, .)` classes CONTINUOUS (it touches u) — class(index(A,e..)) = max(class(A), class(e..)) classes the index expressions INDEPENDENTLY of the array, so the stencil SPLITS. Three materialization points result: nbr_idx + coeff fold at the CONST->CONTINUOUS threshold (compile-time, inline provenance); Kdiff materializes at the DISCRETE->CONTINUOUS threshold (per-event handler, bind provenance). Every node carries an `expect_cadence` assertion the partition pass checks against its derived class. Concrete topology / coefficient values and the byte-identical CONST-folded buffers live in the golden tests/conformance/cadence/manifest.json (this fixture is value-free and validates against the schema with no evaluator, like discrete_variable_refresh.esm).",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.furiosa"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "cadence-partition",
      "stencil",
      "gather-split",
      "discrete-variable",
      "materialization-point",
      "conformance",
      "schema",
      "ess-my4.3.6"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "MixedStencilDiffusion": {
      "index_sets": {
        "cells": { "kind": "interval", "size": 4 },
        "stencil": { "kind": "interval", "size": 3 }
      },
      "variables": {
        "u": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["cells"],
          "description": "Integrated tracer concentration — CONTINUOUS cadence (changes every step)."
        },
        "nbr": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["cells", "stencil"],
          "description": "Neighbour index table (mesh topology / connectivity) — a document-literal arrayed parameter, CONST cadence. Folds into the artifact at compile time (inline provenance)."
        },
        "coeff": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["cells", "stencil"],
          "description": "Per-edge geometric diffusion coefficients — a document-literal arrayed parameter, CONST cadence. Folds into the artifact at compile time (inline provenance)."
        },
        "Kdiff": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["cells"],
          "description": "Reloaded diffusivity field (e.g. from a meteorology source) — shape fixed at setup, values refreshed on a schedule. DISCRETE cadence; materialized into a per-event buffer the hot path reads as a constant (bind provenance).",
          "refresh": {
            "kind": "schedule",
            "interval": 3600.0,
            "initial_offset": 0.0
          }
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(u[i])/dt = sum_{k in stencil} Kdiff[i] * coeff[i,k] * (u[nbr[i,k]] - u[i]). The contraction reduces CONTINUOUS terms over a CONST-fixed range -> a CONTINUOUS hot contraction. The inner topology gather nbr[i,k] is CONST and folds; Kdiff[i] is DISCRETE and materializes; u-loads are CONTINUOUS.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["u", "i"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            },
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 4] }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "expect_cadence": "continuous",
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 4], "k": { "from": "stencil" } },
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "expect_cadence": "continuous",
              "args": [
                {
                  "op": "index",
                  "args": ["Kdiff", "i"],
                  "expect_cadence": "discrete"
                },
                {
                  "op": "*",
                  "expect_cadence": "continuous",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "index",
                      "args": ["coeff", "i", "k"],
                      "expect_cadence": "const"
                    },
                    {
                      "op": "-",
                      "expect_cadence": "continuous",
                      "args": [
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "expect_cadence": "continuous",
                          "args": [
                            "u",
                            {
                              "op": "index",
                              "args": ["nbr", "i", "k"],
                              "expect_cadence": "const"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": ["u", "i"],
                          "expect_cadence": "continuous"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
